defs.docs:
Rational numbers

 ## Compatibility

 The `num-rational` crate is tested for rustc 1.15 and greater.

defs.name: Ratio
defs.docs: Represents the ratio between two numbers.

defs.name: Rational
defs.docs: Alias for a `Ratio` of machine-sized integers.

defs.name: Rational32
defs.docs: Alias for a `Ratio` of 32-bit-sized integers.

defs.name: Rational64
defs.docs: Alias for a `Ratio` of 64-bit-sized integers.

defs.name: new_raw
defs.docs: Creates a `Ratio` without checking for `denom == 0` or reducing.

defs.name: numer
defs.docs: Gets an immutable reference to the numerator.

defs.name: denom
defs.docs: Gets an immutable reference to the denominator.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Creates a new `Ratio`. Fails if `denom` is zero.

defs.name: from_integer
defs.docs: Creates a `Ratio` representing the integer `t`.

defs.name: to_integer
defs.docs: Converts to an integer, rounding towards zero.

defs.name: is_integer
defs.docs: Returns true if the rational number is an integer (denominator is 1).

defs.name: reduced
defs.docs:
Returns a reduced copy of self.

 In general, it is not necessary to use this method, as the only
 method of procuring a non-reduced fraction is through `new_raw`.

defs.name: recip
defs.docs:
Returns the reciprocal.

 Fails if the `Ratio` is zero.

defs.name: floor
defs.docs: Rounds towards minus infinity.

defs.name: ceil
defs.docs: Rounds towards plus infinity.

defs.name: round
defs.docs: Rounds to the nearest integer. Rounds half-way cases away from zero.

defs.name: trunc
defs.docs: Rounds towards zero.

defs.name: fract
defs.docs:
Returns the fractional part of a number, with division rounded towards zero.

 Satisfies `self == self.trunc() + self.fract()`.

defs.name: pow
defs.docs: Raises the `Ratio` to the power of an exponent.
